subSubSection.paragraph:
Male.
Macropterous. Length of forewing 
7‐9 mm
. General color, lime green in life, dirty white in alcohol. Head and pronotum without black markings. Dorsal aspect of epiproct elongate and narrow, subparallel, slightly broader at base, apex evenly rounded, with shallow crenulations (
Figs. 1, 2, 5, 7
); surface bare in apical half, clothed with dense appressed setae in basal half (
Figs. 1‐8
); beak‐ like in lateral view (
Figs. 3, 4, 6, 8
). Stem clothed with fine setae (Figs. 1,5,7).
